## 🔄 Data Flow

### Homepage (Recent Updates Section)

```
1. User visits `/`
   ↓
2. Landing.tsx mounts
   ↓
3. useEffect triggers API call
   → GET /blog-posts?limit=3
   ↓
4. Server queries database
   → SELECT * FROM blog_posts 
     ORDER BY published_at DESC 
     LIMIT 3
   ↓
5. Server returns JSON
   → { posts: [...] }
   ↓
6. Frontend renders blog post cards
   ↓
7. User clicks a card
   → Navigate to /updates/:slug
```

### Individual Post Page

```
1. User visits /updates/season-11-support
   ↓
2. BlogPost.tsx mounts
   ↓
3. React Router extracts slug from URL params
   ↓
4. useEffect triggers API call
   → GET /blog-posts/season-11-support
   ↓
5. Server queries database
   → SELECT * FROM blog_posts 
     WHERE slug = 'season-11-support'
   ↓
6. Server returns JSON
   → { post: {...} }
   ↓
7. Frontend renders full post with HTML content
   ↓
8. useEffect updates page title, meta tags (SEO)
   ↓
9. User clicks "Back to Home"
   → Navigate to /
```

