## 🔒 Security Considerations

### Current Implementation
- ✅ Uses `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` on server (never exposed to frontend)
- ✅ Uses public `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` on frontend (safe to expose)
- ✅ Blog posts are read-only from frontend perspective
- ✅ HTML content is admin-controlled (inserted via Supabase dashboard)

### Row Level Security (RLS)
You should enable RLS on the `blog_posts` table:

```sql
-- Enable RLS
ALTER TABLE blog_posts ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

-- Allow public read access
CREATE POLICY "Anyone can view published posts"
ON blog_posts FOR SELECT
USING (true);

-- Only service role can insert/update/delete
-- (handled automatically by Supabase)
```

### Future Considerations
If you add user-submitted content:
- Sanitize HTML using a library like `DOMPurify`
- Validate input on both frontend and backend
- Implement rate limiting for POST endpoints

