## 🔧 Maintenance Guide

### Adding a New Blog Post

**Option 1: Supabase Dashboard (Recommended)**
1. Go to Supabase Dashboard → Table Editor
2. Open `blog_posts` table
3. Click "Insert row"
4. Fill in fields:
   - `title`: "My New Post"
   - `slug`: "my-new-post" (must be unique, URL-friendly)
   - `description`: "Short summary..."
   - `content`: `<h2>Heading</h2><p>Content...</p>`
   - `tag`: "Feature" | "Update" | "Enhancement"
   - `published_at`: Auto-filled or set custom date
5. Click "Save"

**Option 2: SQL**
```sql
INSERT INTO blog_posts (title, slug, description, content, tag)
VALUES (
  'My New Post',
  'my-new-post',
  'Short summary of the post',
  '<h2>Main Heading</h2><p>Your content here...</p>',
  'Feature'
);
```

### Updating a Blog Post
```sql
UPDATE blog_posts
SET 
  content = '<h2>Updated Content</h2>...',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE slug = 'my-post-slug';
```

### Deleting a Blog Post
```sql
DELETE FROM blog_posts WHERE slug = 'my-post-slug';
```

### Changing Homepage Post Limit
In `/src/app/components/Landing.tsx`:
```typescript
// Change limit=3 to limit=5 (or any number)
`https://${projectId}.supabase.co/functions/v1/make-server-38bddc41/blog-posts?limit=5`
```

### HTML Content Best Practices
When writing blog post content:
- Use semantic HTML: `<h2>`, `<h3>`, `<p>`, `<ul>`, `<ol>`
- Include alt text for images: `<img src="..." alt="Description">`
- Use `<code>` for inline code, `<pre><code>` for code blocks
- Add links with descriptive text: `<a href="...">Click here</a>`

